cs230457@vtaix.cc.vt.edu (Scott Gasch) writes:

>I have a question about a sed.  I need a script that will replace multipal
>spaces in a textfile with a single space.  This is what I tried:
>cat filename | sed 's/[ ]*/ /g' > outfile

This is a "useless use of cat"  (TM :-)

A better _syntax_ would be:

sed 's/[ ]*/ /g' < filename > outfile

or even

sed 's/[ ]*/ /g' filename > outfile

>This seems to hang sed...  I also tried:
>cat filename | sed 's/\[ ]*\/ /g' > outfile
>To which sed replies that the command is garbled.

Now, to solve your problem, try this:

sed -e 's/  */ /g' filename > outfile

Cheers
Tony
