That's the way I'd do it too, though I usually put a space and a tab in
square brackets for each of your arrowed spaces, viz

        s/[<tab><sp][<tab><sp]*/ /g

since most files *I* see have a mixture.

A good way of testing regular expressions is to edit a COPY of the file
you want to transform with vi and issue the s/../../ commands manually
until you find one you like.

Martin

